      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing performed at minimum two load levels or two environmental conditions to characterize response envelope.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed exclusively under the single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending condition (axial compressive load with 10° offset). No alternative load magnitudes, rates, or environmental conditions (e.g., wet, elevated temperature) were evaluated. Achieved level 1 is below required level 2; this is the one factor below threshold, noted as a limitation in the decision record.",
      "factorStatusNote": "Below required level — single test condition only. Accepted given corroborating literature and regulatory precedent for ASTM F1717 as the standard acceptance test for spinal implants."
