      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to clinical failure modes (fatigue initiation governed by peak stress, construct stiffness governs load sharing).",
      "rationale": "Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified by ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to clinical performance: stiffness governs load sharing between implant and bone graft; yield force represents onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm approximates catastrophic failure load. All three QoIs are directly extractable from both FEA and bench test data without transformation."
    },
