    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for a Medium model risk, Medium model influence, Medium decision consequence context of use. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is accepted on the basis of: (1) ASTM F1717 is the regulatory standard acceptance test for spinal implant constructs and single-condition testing is industry norm; (2) corroborating published literature supports the adequacy of static compression-bending as a discriminating test for this device class; (3) the three primary QoIs all satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%). The overall credibility profile supports use of the FEA framework for regulatory submission in support of the non-cannulated pedicle screw design.",
